First version, stand alone for now, start script for clustering and configuring external database will follow shortly.

Build with:

	sudo docker build -t test/liferay .

The docker image will expose two ports 22 and 8080 for the users to interact with.

To spawn an instance of Liferay Portal 6.2.0-CE you need to 
-----------------------------------------------------------

    docker run -p <host_port>:22 -p<host_port>:8080 -d test/liferay 

